JRE vs. JDK:
1. Java Runtime Environment (JRE)
    - Required to run Java apps 
    - End-users normally require only the JRE 
2. Java Development Kit (JDK)
    - Provides tools required to create Java apps 
    - Developers normally require the JDK 
    - JDK installation includes JRE 
-----------
Creating and Running Java Apps:
xyz.java (Java Source Code) -> Java Development Kit tools
-> Java Apps (platform-independent byte codes)
-> Java Runtime Environment
-> Host Environment (Windows/Linux/Mac/Browser/Android)